  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">COOPABA is one of 6 cooperatives participating in the second phase of the 20at-8529 rice project. COOPABA is a young cooperative structure of around 7 years old with many ambitions for the processing and marketing of agricultural products. Created to meet the critical needs of members in difficulty accessing the remunerative market and the sale of raw agricultural products. This young cooperative holds by different defined strategies to penetrate the industrial market of Bralima thanks to the support of Agriterra and work on the quality of table rice.
To this end  COOPABA is resolutely committed to improving production through the strategy of grouping its members at the base into associative groups and to exploit model fields in each group where new agricultural methods and techniques have been made to encourage members to increase their production. The efforts made by a total of 133 potential member producers and 7 agents prove the commitment of this cooperative enough to meet the market needs that Agriterra had just negotiated with Bralima for agricultural producers in the Ruzizi plain in general and for those of COOPABA in particular. For the year 2019  COOPABA had delivered to the Bralima a total of 300 tons of white rice as its purchase order required and for this year 2020 COOPABA will deliver a total of 480 tons of rice still to the Bralima.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Organiser un audit des &#xE9;tats financiers de 2019Organiser des rencontres entre les membres des organes (CA  CS et AG)Installer des champs &#xE9;coles paysansSuivre l&apos;adoption de la GIFS dans les champs des membres.Restituer les formations sur la gestion financi&#xE8;re  gestion de la coop&#xE9;rative  gouvernance avec les agents et autres membres de la coop&#xE9;rative.Organiser des rencontres d&apos;affaires sur le contrat Bralima au d&#xE9;but pour fixer les objectifs et &#xE0; la fin des livraisons pour l&apos;&#xE9;valuation du niveau de r&#xE9;alisation de ces derniersSensibiliser des membres des organes &#xE0; int&#xE9;grer les jeunes dans la coop&#xE9;rative : Sensibiliser les jeunes &#xE0; int&#xE9;grer la coop&#xE9;rative  tenir les rencontres avec les membres des organes  revisiter le texte.Organiser la journ&#xE9;e porte ouverte</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to facilitate the cooperative to deliver 480 tonnes of rice to Bralima  access financing and improve the income level of members.</narrative>
  </description>
